  <prompt>
    <goal>Replace hardcoded `ModelName = "gpt-4o"` in GenericAnalysisHandler with a model resolution chain: node-level override â†’ ModelSelector routing â†’ global default.</goal>
    <context>
      GenericAnalysisHandler currently ignores the ModelSelector service and context.ModelDeploymentId. The ModelSelector has operation-type routing (classificationâ†’gpt-4o-mini, reasoningâ†’o1-mini, generationâ†’gpt-4o) but it's only used by BuilderService. This fix wires it into playbook execution.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Resolution chain: context.ModelDeploymentId â†’ ModelSelector.SelectModel(operationType) â†’ options.DefaultModel
      - Must not break existing playbooks (if no node override and no operationType, falls through to default)
      - Verify ModelSelector operation type routing is correct
      - Update all tool handlers that hardcode model names (not just GenericAnalysisHandler)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      .claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md
      .claude/constraints/ai.md
      docs/guides/SPAARKE-AI-ARCHITECTURE.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read `Services/Ai/Handlers/GenericAnalysisHandler.cs` â€” find the hardcoded ModelName assignment</step>
    <step>Read `Services/Ai/ModelSelector.cs` â€” understand operation-type routing and available types</step>
    <step>Search all tool handlers for hardcoded model names: `grep -r "ModelName = " Services/Ai/`</step>
    <step>Implement model resolution chain in GenericAnalysisHandler:
      ```
      ModelName = context.ModelDeploymentId
          ?? _modelSelector.SelectModel(context.OperationType)
          ?? _options.DefaultModel
      ```</step>
    <step>Apply same pattern to any other handlers with hardcoded models</step>
    <step>Verify ModelSelector.SelectModel returns correct models per OperationType enum</step>
    <step>Write unit tests for the resolution chain (each level of fallback)</step>
    <step>Test: run a classification action â†’ should use gpt-4o-mini; run analysis â†’ should use gpt-4o</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>Bash, Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Grep</tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>GenericAnalysisHandler using model resolution chain</output>
    <output>All handlers updated (no more hardcoded model names)</output>
    <output>Unit tests for model resolution</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
